item.title: Orphaned case!
item.dc:creator: @snowycards snowycards
item.description:
@snowycards wrote:

[quote=“woofdawg23, post:1, topic:166867”]Ok whenever i try compiling my source i get this error.

client.java:29804: orphaned case case 1533: ^ client.java:30176: illegal start of expression public boolean CheckForSkillUse4(int Item) { ^ 2 errors Files Compiled Successfully! Press any key to continue . . .
plz help will reward ya.[/quote]

ok i had these same problems a ton of times!
for the orphaned case, you are DEFINATELY missing a bracket somewhere, if you can post your case 1533 then hopefully i can help you, for the illegal start of expression thats easy

search for public boolean CheckForSkillUse4(int Item) {
and before it, put an enter, and a }. keep on putting another bracket until the error goes away, if you get 100 errrors, remove the bracket

It means that :

Is already somewhere else/being used/in the same place/case.

Solution:
Simply search :

Then delete one of them.
